HTML Research

History:
HTML:Hyper Text Markup Language
Most widely used language on Web to develop web pages.
Created by Berners-Lee 1991

Hypertext: Way in which Web pages (HTML documents) are linked together.
% link available on a webpage is called Hypertext.

HTML = Markup Language
Use HTML to simply "mark-up" a text document with tags that tell a Web browser how to structure it to display.
Originally, HTML to define the structure of documents (i.e headings, paragraphs, lists)
Now, HTML to format web pages with different <tags>(</closingtag>) available in HTML language.

HTML:
TAGS
ELEMENTS
ATTRIBUTES (more in depth  (name & value) elements)
SEMANTICS(i.e. div/class) - Sections/Categories for layout (i.e. aside, nav, footer, header - can use id for this too)
